Spain’s Defense Minstry May Extend Payments, Cinco Dias Says

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-10-20T07:45:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/spain-s-defense-minstry-may-extend-payments-cinco-dias-says.html
Spain ’s  Defense Ministry  has
proposed measures, including an extension of payments from 5 to
15 years, as a way to improve its financial situation,  Cinco
Dias  said, citing reports sent by the ministry to parliament.  The ministry, which has 26.5 billion euros ($36.3 billion)
of debt due to weapon purchasing programs, would extend its
payments calendar to 2030, five more years than the current
calendar, or even as many as 15 years more till 2040, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  